HTML

HTML (Hypertext markup language) is the standard language for creating web pages . 
this tutorial will cover the essitials concepts to get you started with HTML.

getting started

HTML structure 

DOCTYPE Declaration
<!DOCTYPE html>
this declaration tells browsers that this is an HTML5 document 

HTML Element
<html lang="en">...</html>
the root element of HTML page. the lang atribute specifies the language . 

Head Element
<head>...</head>
contains meta-information about the document that isn't displayed 

Meta Tags 
<meta charset="UTF8">
specifies the charater enclosing

<meta name="viewport" content="width=device=width,inital-scale=1.0">
makes the page repronsive for moblie update

title Element
<title> page title </title>
sets the title of the page (appears in browsers tab)

Body Element
<body>...</body>
contains al the visible content of the web pages 

Text Element
Heading
<h1>main heading</h1>
the largest heading 

<h2> subheading</h2>
second -level heading

<h3></h3>,<h4></h4>,<h5></h5>,and <h6></h6> are respectively
smaller heading
<h6>smallest heading</h6>

paragraphs
<p>this is a paragraph of text . HTML will automatically  </p>